Text.Value: *SCREECH!*
*Caw!*
*Your repeated approach has ruffled the eagle's feathers the wrong way.*
*The eagle eyes you warily, but doesn't attack.*
I'm just interested in the big device, I promise to not meddle with the nest.
Ugh, fine. Xavier! XAVIER! Don't talk to it. It might have germs.
You would accuse ME of a CRIME in my OWN HOME? Outrageous!
Attack.
It's not your nest. You stole it from the little bird who used to live here.
Turn away from the eagle as you approach, indicating that you are not interested in its nest.
*The eagle seems satisfied, but keeps a watchful eye on you.*
Leave.
Nest-meddling lies! I thought as much!
Leave.
You've been warned plenty! GET OUT!
Attack.
INTRUDER! In MY NEST! This area was meant to be SAFE! Xavier, get behind mummy.

Text.Value: Please, get out of my nest. You'll give Xavier ideas.
Back away slowly.
*The giant eagle regards you with disdain.*
